header.gameNote: WYOMING JIM THORPE CLASSIC AT LARAMIE WY

article.headline: Portland St. 66, Louisiana Tech 48
article.story: LARAMIE, Wyo. -- Charles Odum scored a career-high 27 points to lead Portland State over Louisiana Tech 66-48 on Saturday in the round-robin Jim Thorpe Classic. Chehales Tapscott added 11 points along with career highs of 14 rebounds and four steals for Portland State (3-2). Louisiana Tech (2-2) was paced by Michale Kyser with 10 points. Odum made three driving layups and two free throws to key a 20-3 spurt that turned a 19-9 Portland State deficit into a 29-22 lead. Louisiana Tech was still within seven, 44-37, at the 9:11 mark after a putback by Kyser, but Tapscott sparked a 14-0 surge with five points and the Vikings were not threatened the rest of the way. The two teams combined to shoot 4 of 41 from beyond the 3-point line, including 0 for 22 in the first half.
